Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State has tasked investors coming into the state on accountability and transparency. He made the statement at a dinner organized in his honour by some investors that, “My administration has thrown wide open the state to both local and international investors, I urge prospective investors to conduct their activities in the state with all sense of accountability and transparency.” He warned that he is coming to the table with clean hands and that investors must therefore put the interest of Nasarawa State above personal interest. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYMDROM DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE He disclosed that his administration will provide all the necessary infrastructure to facilitate the activities of investors, stressing that the state will collaborate with security agencies to ensure there is peace and security for businesses to thrive. FG, Nasarawa to partner on industrialisation Benue Gov wants CBN to cut down interest rates on loans FG, Nasarawa govt partner on industrialisation Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin